<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The neotype is designated for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lewis, 1895" authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Athemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Athemus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Athemus</taxonomicName>
(s.str.) maculithorax Wang &amp; Yang, 1992 here, according to the loss of the type, and for allowing a comparision based on most of the criteria (ICZN, 4th, article 75.3). The 
<normalizedToken originalValue="latter’s">latter's</normalizedToken>
name was replaced by 
<taxonomicName authority="Lewis, 1895" authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Athemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Athemus wangi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangi">Athemus wangi</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Svihla, V" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Basiliensia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="155 - 238" title="New taxa of the subfamily Cantharinae (Coleoptera, Cantharidae) from southeastern Asia with notes on other species." volume="26" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Švihla">Svihla</normalizedToken>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
and now is placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lycocerus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kazantsev, SV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="234 - 298" title="Cantharidae." year="2007">Kazantsev and Brancucci 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Having examined the lectotype of 
